<item>
            <title>[TIKA-366] Increase buffer size for mime type sniffing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-366</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-357&quot; title=&quot;Increase buffer size for meta tag sniffing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-357&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-357&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to address a similar problem for charset detection, I found an issue with mime identification having to do with the same general problem. Tika right now only deals with the first MimeTypes#getMinLength() bytes of a magic header to do the sniffing of mime type. With the example file attached from Ken Krugler, it&apos;s clear that the current min length size of 4 * 1024 bytes isn&apos;t enough. Extending it to 8K (8 * 1024 bytes) addresses this issue and seems to open up more opportunity for mime detection at little overhead cost.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;My local MacBook pro laptop.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
